Bachelor's degree in Mechanical, Electrical, or Plumbing Engineering or a related field.
Professional Engineering (PE) license is a plus.
Proven experience in MEP engineering, preferably in construction or building design projects.
Proficiency in MEP design software such as AutoCAD, Revit, or similar tools.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills for effective collaboration with team members and clients.
Knowledge of relevant codes, standards, and regulations related to MEP systems.
